description.narrative: (Indonesia): The overarching objective of this IM is the provision of innovative and improved service delivery by local governments to citizens. USAID focuses on the governance of service delivery in three sectors: education; health services and; and local business. Activities under this IM address both demand and supply side aspects of service delivery. These investments will result in strengthened accountability mechanisms that improve local government responses to citizens' needs. USAID works through local institutions to build their capacity and foster sustainable partnerships with local government. This solidifies the links between stimulation of demand for good services through active civil society engagement and improved local government response. This is the final year of activity under this IM. Along with the activities noted above, particular focus will be placed on expanding good service delivery practices among sub national governments by leveraging the role of provincial and national governments. In this final year, targeted investments in Papua will raise district government capacity and increase public participation in service delivery improvements.Expected results through the IM include:-District government staff awareness of health care rights increased.-Citizen engagement in the planning and monitoring of public services increased.-Access to information on good practices in public service delivery improved.
